  <p>Let's step back a minute for an overhead view: Office jobs quite naturally tend to be located in office buildings. For hardcore city dwellers, those buildings can get <em>really</em> big.</p>

  <p>So what will future office buildings and plazas look like? One heartening 21st-century trend is that big buildings and city spaces are a lot more eco-friendly than they used to be. Architecture changes slowly, so near-future changes are likely to be small and iterative. Consider the European startup concept called <a href="https://greencitysolutions.de/en/solutions/#section2">CityTree</a>, a mobile moss structure designed to scrub pollutants from the air in city parks and commercial plazas.</p>

  <p>For the eye-popping far-future stuff, be sure to check out eVolo magazine's annual <a href="http://www.evolo.us/category/competition/">Skyscraper Competition</a>, which invites architects to cut loose and dream up incredible space-age buildings of the future. The concept skyscraper pictured here, runner-up winner in 2017, envisions a colossal <a href="http://www.evolo.us/featured/vertical-factories-in-megacities/">vertical factory</a> where materials are perpetually recycled through integrated green spaces.</p>

